1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:34,684 --> 00:01:36,572
(Nine years ago)

3
00:01:36,572 --> 00:01:37,492
Sir, bring the food.

4
00:01:37,591 --> 00:01:38,091
Alright.

5
00:01:38,091 --> 00:01:39,171
What's so funny?

6
00:01:39,171 --> 00:01:39,731
Sir,

7
00:01:40,132 --> 00:01:40,932
bring us a beer.

8
00:01:41,412 --> 00:01:42,332
I thought of

9
00:01:42,332 --> 00:01:43,891
that Wilson woman's face earlier.

10
00:01:44,171 --> 00:01:44,772
Did you see?

11
00:01:44,772 --> 00:01:45,692
When I took her deal,

12
00:01:45,692 --> 00:01:47,852
her hair literally stood on end.

13
00:01:48,451 --> 00:01:50,132
She was so mad
that her face was twisted.

14
00:01:50,772 --> 00:01:52,251
Keep it down, will you?

15
00:01:52,572 --> 00:01:54,772
She lost several deals
she thought were in the bag.

16
00:01:55,212 --> 00:01:57,412
Then let her take them back.

17
00:01:57,531 --> 00:01:59,291
Liang Danning, are you drunk?

18
00:01:59,291 --> 00:02:01,132
Quite a bit.

19
00:02:07,251 --> 00:02:09,251
So you're the one
who stole my sister's deal.

20
00:02:09,571 --> 00:02:12,012
Thought you'd be some goddess,

21
00:02:12,251 --> 00:02:14,091
but you're just an eyesore.

22
00:02:16,892 --> 00:02:18,531
Eyesore or not,

23
00:02:18,892 --> 00:02:21,411
if I can snag deals, I'm a good eyesore.

24
00:02:21,932 --> 00:02:23,732
Unlike some clumsy fool

25
00:02:24,251 --> 00:02:26,452
who can't steal deals
but just cries by the floats.

26
00:02:26,452 --> 00:02:27,571
What did you say?

27
00:02:29,612 --> 00:02:30,971
Let's not waste words on them.

28
00:02:31,131 --> 00:02:33,251
You stole Julie's
30,000-yuan deal today.

29
00:02:33,772 --> 00:02:34,691
The commission is 500.

30
00:02:35,332 --> 00:02:36,772
Hand over that 500.

31
00:02:36,772 --> 00:02:37,772
500?

32
00:02:39,131 --> 00:02:41,691
Then clearly, she's not the fool,
but you are.

33
00:02:41,932 --> 00:02:42,772
You dare insult me?

34
00:02:42,772 --> 00:02:43,691
Do you know who I am?

35
00:02:43,691 --> 00:02:44,691
Couldn't care less.

36
00:02:44,691 --> 00:02:45,691
Alright, enough.

37
00:02:45,691 --> 00:02:46,691
Girls,

38
00:02:47,052 --> 00:02:48,851
we're all just trying
to make a living here.

39
00:02:49,492 --> 00:02:51,492
Don't get upset over small stuff.

40
00:02:51,772 --> 00:02:53,332
Not worth it, right?

41
00:02:53,332 --> 00:02:55,251
Stealing a 30,000 deal is 'small stuff'?

42
00:02:55,251 --> 00:02:57,851
This isn't the first time
she's stolen a deal from me.

43
00:02:58,411 --> 00:02:59,492
Maybe you're just dumb.

44
00:02:59,571 --> 00:03:00,332
Enough talk.

45
00:03:00,411 --> 00:03:01,212
Give us 500,

46
00:03:01,212 --> 00:03:02,851
or neither of you leaves tonight.

47
00:03:02,932 --> 00:03:04,012
500?

48
00:03:04,212 --> 00:03:06,052
You've got to be joking.

49
00:03:06,052 --> 00:03:06,971
We won't get 500

50
00:03:06,971 --> 00:03:08,932
even by selling 30,000, alright?

51
00:03:10,131 --> 00:03:10,932
How about this?

52
00:03:11,332 --> 00:03:13,971
We'll treat you to a late-night snack.

53
00:03:13,971 --> 00:03:14,691
Deal?

54
00:03:15,851 --> 00:03:16,691
Why treat them?

55
00:03:16,691 --> 00:03:18,131
Who wants your snack? Pay up.

56
00:03:18,971 --> 00:03:19,932
Buzz off.

57
00:03:31,691 --> 00:03:32,571
Who's an eyesore?

58
00:03:32,971 --> 00:03:34,052
Who's an eyesore?

59
00:03:38,091 --> 00:03:39,212
Who's an eyesore?

60
00:03:44,612 --> 00:03:45,172
Zhao Mei?

61
00:03:46,012 --> 00:03:46,571
Zhao Mei?

