98
00:05:32,131 --> 00:05:33,412
5,000. It'll be enough.

99
00:05:36,972 --> 00:05:37,691
Got it.

100
00:05:45,179 --> 00:05:47,387
(Assets: 18,517.00)

101
00:05:58,052 --> 00:05:58,852
It's transferred.

102
00:05:59,412 --> 00:06:00,052
Okay.

103
00:06:07,532 --> 00:06:08,532
Wrong again.

104
00:06:30,172 --> 00:06:32,852
Is Zhang Changfu one of our suppliers?

105
00:06:33,052 --> 00:06:34,532
He's both a supplier and a client.

106
00:06:36,172 --> 00:06:37,811
So the money he earns from us

107
00:06:37,811 --> 00:06:38,932
ends up back with us.

108
00:06:39,612 --> 00:06:41,131
That's a good cycle.

109
00:06:41,492 --> 00:06:44,131
I've arranged a gathering
at Cocoon tonight. He'll be there too.

110
00:06:44,732 --> 00:06:45,691
I'll introduce you.

111
00:06:45,932 --> 00:06:46,811
Great.

112
00:06:48,052 --> 00:06:48,852
Thanks, boss.

113
00:06:49,852 --> 00:06:52,492
Song Qiang
is in the wholesale seafood business.

114
00:06:53,052 --> 00:06:54,172
He keeps a low profile

115
00:06:54,172 --> 00:06:55,492
and never attends any events.

116
00:06:55,732 --> 00:06:58,292
But he places one or two orders
every quarter.

117
00:06:59,292 --> 00:07:01,412
Tough guy, few words. I like that.

118
00:07:02,852 --> 00:07:05,932
Didn't expect getting bitten by a dog
would land me two clients.

119
00:07:07,052 --> 00:07:09,612
I suddenly feel like that dog bite
wasn't for nothing.

120
00:07:10,612 --> 00:07:12,852
You took the hit for the company.
Fair's fair.

121
00:07:13,292 --> 00:07:13,811
