158
00:09:12,451 --> 00:09:13,252
or champagne?

159
00:09:14,851 --> 00:09:15,932
Notice any changes?

160
00:09:17,611 --> 00:09:18,691
Zhao Mei?

161
00:09:20,491 --> 00:09:22,172
She's sitting ahead of Tang now.

162
00:09:23,172 --> 00:09:24,172
They're promoting her?

163
00:09:24,172 --> 00:09:24,731
To what?

164
00:09:25,811 --> 00:09:26,731
Upwards.

165
00:09:27,252 --> 00:09:28,851
They're making her Sales Director?

166
00:09:29,292 --> 00:09:29,792
Obviously.

167
00:09:31,611 --> 00:09:32,932
Why wasn't I born a woman?

168
00:09:40,292 --> 00:09:40,932
Good afternoon.

169
00:09:40,932 --> 00:09:42,292
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

170
00:09:46,412 --> 00:09:47,691
Let's begin then.

171
00:09:47,932 --> 00:09:48,432
Okay.

172
00:09:49,731 --> 00:09:50,932
Why don't you start?

173
00:09:51,731 --> 00:09:52,372
Okay.

174
00:09:54,132 --> 00:09:55,211
As you all know,

175
00:09:55,932 --> 00:09:58,611
I rarely attend
specific departmental meetings.

176
00:09:59,412 --> 00:10:00,932
But being here today...

177
00:10:03,372 --> 00:10:04,451
Recently, the company,

178
00:10:04,971 --> 00:10:06,611
especially your Sales Department,

179
00:10:07,372 --> 00:10:08,971
has had one incident after another.

180
00:10:10,331 --> 00:10:11,052
Therefore,

181
00:10:11,451 --> 00:10:13,412
many colleagues have some

182
00:10:14,132 --> 00:10:14,652
doubts

183
00:10:15,971 --> 00:10:17,372
or suspicions.

184
00:10:18,211 --> 00:10:19,132
That's quite normal.

185
00:10:21,372 --> 00:10:22,611
For this meeting,

186
00:10:23,491 --> 00:10:25,132
I just want to say three things.

187
00:10:26,892 --> 00:10:28,372
From an HR perspective,

188
00:10:29,211 --> 00:10:30,611
sales work

189
00:10:30,932 --> 00:10:33,091
is the top priority of our company.

190
00:10:33,851 --> 00:10:34,728
It's the first point.

191
00:10:36,052 --> 00:10:36,611
Second point:

192
00:10:37,892 --> 00:10:40,052
Promotion is part of sales.

193
00:10:40,851 --> 00:10:41,811
Just like

194
00:10:42,571 --> 00:10:43,611
live-streaming sales,

195
00:10:43,971 --> 00:10:47,252
which directly convert promotion
into sales volume.

196
00:10:48,252 --> 00:10:48,851
So,

197
00:10:50,412 --> 00:10:51,971
promotion is sales.

198
00:10:52,971 --> 00:10:54,132
Our company possesses

199
00:10:54,132 --> 00:10:56,132
the industry's top-tier

200
00:10:56,132 --> 00:10:57,731
promotion personnel.

201
00:10:58,971 --> 00:11:00,892
How to seamlessly integrate

202
00:11:01,132 --> 00:11:02,971
promotions and sales

203
00:11:03,132 --> 00:11:04,491
requires your Sales Department's

204
00:11:04,971 --> 00:11:06,211
extensive exploration.

205
00:11:08,132 --> 00:11:08,731
Third,

206
00:11:10,091 --> 00:11:12,372
all the negative news reports

207
00:11:12,971 --> 00:11:14,611
will fuel our future drive.

208
00:11:15,412 --> 00:11:16,932
I leave you

209
00:11:18,611 --> 00:11:19,412
with this thought.

210
00:11:39,971 --> 00:11:41,052
Are you implying

211
00:11:41,491 --> 00:11:43,772
that Zhao Mei,
who apologized to that sales lady,

212
00:11:44,372 --> 00:11:46,052
and your former supervisor,

213
00:11:46,052 --> 00:11:47,892
who sexually harassed the same girl,

214
00:11:47,892 --> 00:11:49,491
having an affair? Is it true?

215
00:11:49,491 --> 00:11:50,731
Of course, it's true.

216
00:11:50,731 --> 00:11:52,132
Why would I lie?

217
00:11:52,252 --> 00:11:54,811
Zhao Mei was
originally just a sales lady.

218
00:11:54,971 --> 00:11:55,971
Without the connections,

219
00:11:55,971 --> 00:11:57,491
how could she climb so high?

220
00:11:58,091 --> 00:11:59,132
You know what?

221
00:11:59,412 --> 00:12:00,971
I saw Zhao Mei

222
00:12:00,971 --> 00:12:02,971
come out of Xu Yuntian's room.

223
00:12:03,731 --> 00:12:04,772
Seriously?

224
00:12:04,971 --> 00:12:05,731
What did you say?

225
00:12:06,372 --> 00:12:07,252
You personally saw

226
00:12:07,252 --> 00:12:09,132
Zhao Mei come out of Xu Yuntian's room?

227
00:12:09,331 --> 00:12:09,851
Yeah.

228
00:12:11,052 --> 00:12:12,211
When exactly did you see it?

229
00:12:12,652 --> 00:12:14,292
What year, month, and day?

230
00:12:14,292 --> 00:12:15,971
Which location and which room?

231
00:12:16,971 --> 00:12:18,372
Why should I tell you?

232
00:12:18,372 --> 00:12:19,611
Because she's my colleague

233
00:12:19,611 --> 00:12:20,851
and my best friend.

234
00:12:21,292 --> 00:12:22,571
You'd better explain yourself.

235
00:12:22,892 --> 00:12:23,811
Otherwise,

236
00:12:24,252 --> 00:12:25,491
you're spreading rumors.

237
00:12:25,851 --> 00:12:27,012
Who's spreading rumors?

238
00:12:27,012 --> 00:12:27,932
They shared a room

239
00:12:27,932 --> 00:12:29,331
during the Dongshan team-building.

240
00:12:29,971 --> 00:12:31,252
You saw it yourself?

241
00:12:31,412 --> 00:12:32,611
Yes, I saw it myself.

242
00:12:33,731 --> 00:12:34,231
Alright.

243
00:12:45,772 --> 00:12:47,331
Mr. Xu, this is Liang Danning.

244
00:12:47,971 --> 00:12:50,412
Yu Wei'e claims that during
last year's Dongshan team-building,

245
00:12:50,412 --> 00:12:53,252
he personally saw you and Zhao Mei
sharing a room. Is that true?

246
00:12:53,932 --> 00:12:54,731
Nonsense.

247
00:12:55,252 --> 00:12:56,772
Put that brat on the phone.

248
00:13:01,611 --> 00:13:04,372
Mr. Xu, that is pure slander.

249
00:13:04,532 --> 00:13:06,811
Someone else said it. Not me.

250
00:13:06,811 --> 00:13:08,451
Someone else? Who?

251
00:13:09,132 --> 00:13:10,012
I was drunk.

252
00:13:10,012 --> 00:13:11,731
I was drunk, okay, Mr. Xu?

253
00:13:11,731 --> 00:13:12,971
I'm so sorry.

254
00:13:13,132 --> 00:13:13,971
My apologies.

255
00:13:14,611 --> 00:13:16,091
I can't control my mouth.

256
00:13:16,091 --> 00:13:17,052
If it happens again,

257
00:13:17,052 --> 00:13:18,731
how about I send you my head?

258
00:13:19,252 --> 00:13:20,412
Mr. Xu, I'm so sorry.

259
00:13:24,491 --> 00:13:26,292
So you admit you were spreading rumors?

260
00:13:28,012 --> 00:13:29,372
I was just joking.

261
00:13:29,652 --> 00:13:30,772
Is this really necessary?

262
00:13:30,772 --> 00:13:31,491
Absolutely.

263
00:13:32,252 --> 00:13:33,252
Joke about me? Fine.

264
00:13:33,252 --> 00:13:34,851
But making jokes about Zhao Mei?

265
00:13:35,172 --> 00:13:35,731
No.

266
00:13:37,731 --> 00:13:38,231
Fine.

267
00:13:38,731 --> 00:13:39,731
I'm sorry to you.

268
00:13:40,132 --> 00:13:41,091
And to your friend.

269
00:13:41,292 --> 00:13:41,971
Satisfied now?

270
00:13:42,211 --> 00:13:43,252
Not yet.

271
00:13:59,491 --> 00:14:01,012
Drink all ten glasses of liquor.

272
00:14:01,252 --> 00:14:02,211
Then we're done.

273
00:14:03,292 --> 00:14:04,811
Ten glasses shouldn't be a problem.

274
00:14:07,132 --> 00:14:07,632
Okay.

275
00:14:25,731 --> 00:14:27,252
Bottoms up on all ten glasses.

276
00:14:34,731 --> 00:14:35,851
Truly impressive!

277
00:14:35,851 --> 00:14:36,451
Are we good?

278
00:14:36,571 --> 00:14:37,491
Sure.

279
00:14:47,932 --> 00:14:48,652
Come on.

280
00:14:49,132 --> 00:14:50,532
I immediately called Xu Yuntian.

281
00:14:50,932 --> 00:14:52,132
Then I made Yu Wei'e

282
00:14:53,091 --> 00:14:54,691
down all ten glasses.

283
00:14:55,331 --> 00:14:56,491
He was reacting to alcohol,

284
00:14:56,491 --> 00:14:57,772
his face turning red.

285
00:14:58,211 --> 00:14:59,372
Right in front of me,

286
00:14:59,372 --> 00:15:00,932
Dong Yue, and everyone else,

287
00:15:00,932 --> 00:15:02,052
he spoke of you viciously.

288
00:15:02,532 --> 00:15:03,491
If I let him off,

289
00:15:03,491 --> 00:15:05,012
what would that make me?

290
00:15:05,652 --> 00:15:07,331
He'll probably
hold a grudge against you.

291
00:15:07,611 --> 00:15:08,611
Let him hold a grudge.

292
00:15:08,611 --> 00:15:09,971
It's superficial peace anyway.

293
00:15:10,491 --> 00:15:11,892
What would you two like today?

294
00:15:12,372 --> 00:15:13,571
The rice paper rolls.

295
00:15:13,571 --> 00:15:14,491
The fried spring rolls.

296
00:15:14,491 --> 00:15:15,772
- Okay.
- And two iced lemon teas.

297
00:15:15,772 --> 00:15:16,272
Hold on.

298
00:15:17,331 --> 00:15:18,012
I'll treat you.

299
00:15:18,611 --> 00:15:19,851
Of course, you're treating.

300
00:15:20,211 --> 00:15:20,731
By the way,

301
00:15:21,091 --> 00:15:22,292
I forgot to ask you last time.

302
00:15:22,292 --> 00:15:22,892
Two of these.

303
00:15:22,892 --> 00:15:25,851
How come Qi Youlan suddenly
supported you at the sales meeting?

304
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:27,652
I gave Barry all the client files

305
00:15:27,731 --> 00:15:29,091
that Xu gave me.

306
00:15:29,851 --> 00:15:30,772
What?

307
00:15:34,908 --> 00:15:39,912
(Two days ago)

308
00:15:40,491 --> 00:15:41,731
I didn't expect that Xu Yuntian

309
00:15:41,731 --> 00:15:43,571
would hand over all his clients to you.

310
00:15:44,731 --> 00:15:46,172
And you've given all their files

311
00:15:46,172 --> 00:15:46,851
to me.

312
00:15:48,292 --> 00:15:49,252
What's your intention?

313
00:15:49,772 --> 00:15:51,132
I have no intention.

314
00:15:52,571 --> 00:15:54,132
I think these are less like clients

315
00:15:54,132 --> 00:15:56,012
that Mr. Xu left for me

316
00:15:56,132 --> 00:15:57,172
and more like wealth

317
00:15:57,611 --> 00:15:59,252
he left for the company.

318
00:16:00,611 --> 00:16:01,331
Well,

319
00:16:01,611 --> 00:16:03,731
I'm just a promotions manager.

320
00:16:04,091 --> 00:16:06,052
It's hard for me
to maintain these clients well.

321
00:16:06,292 --> 00:16:07,932
So I decided to give them to you

322
00:16:08,211 --> 00:16:09,571
for you to allocate reasonably.

323
00:16:12,571 --> 00:16:14,211
But that's your entire livelihood.

324
00:16:14,211 --> 00:16:15,052
You just gave him?

325
00:16:15,412 --> 00:16:16,331
I figured

326
00:16:16,932 --> 00:16:18,772
if I couldn't gain Barry's trust,

327
00:16:18,772 --> 00:16:19,611
I had no future

328
00:16:19,811 --> 00:16:20,611
back at the company.

329
00:16:21,012 --> 00:16:22,632
Holding the client list was pointless,

330
00:16:23,012 --> 00:16:24,851
so I used it as my ticket in

331
00:16:24,851 --> 00:16:25,491
and gambled.

332
00:16:26,892 --> 00:16:28,132
It seems to be working now.

333
00:16:29,971 --> 00:16:32,132
Since Xu Yuntian
left his clients to you,

334
00:16:32,331 --> 00:16:34,571
it shows he thinks
you can maintain them well.

335
00:16:35,731 --> 00:16:36,412
Right?

336
00:16:36,611 --> 00:16:37,412
Of course.

337
00:16:38,491 --> 00:16:40,491
You're the head
of the Promotions Department,

338
00:16:41,012 --> 00:16:42,252
but promotions themselves

339
00:16:42,252 --> 00:16:43,971
are a very important part of sales.

340
00:16:44,451 --> 00:16:44,971
I think,

341
00:16:44,971 --> 00:16:47,252
at the next sales meeting,
we should emphasize

342
00:16:47,491 --> 00:16:48,372
this point.

343
00:16:48,971 --> 00:16:51,052
Does this mean the big bosses

344
00:16:51,292 --> 00:16:53,292
support you taking Mr. Xu's role?

345
00:16:56,532 --> 00:16:57,611
I can only say

346
00:16:58,216 --> 00:16:59,080
they don't oppose.

347
00:17:00,851 --> 00:17:01,932
Consider it my ticket in.

348
00:17:02,772 --> 00:17:03,731
That works too.

349
00:17:04,172 --> 00:17:05,332
Still a big step forward.

350
00:17:05,892 --> 00:17:06,392
Girl,

351
00:17:07,211 --> 00:17:08,372
go ahead. I'm relying on you.

352
00:17:09,011 --> 00:17:10,011
Okay.

353
00:17:11,451 --> 00:17:12,051
Ladies,

354
00:17:12,051 --> 00:17:13,731
your rice paper rolls and spring rolls

355
00:17:13,731 --> 00:17:14,231
are ready.

356
00:17:14,572 --> 00:17:15,251
I'll go get them.

357
00:17:17,731 --> 00:17:18,491
Enjoy your meal.

358
00:17:18,652 --> 00:17:20,051
Okay, thank you.

359
00:17:25,771 --> 00:17:27,572
But now I'm a bit worried about you.

360
00:17:28,691 --> 00:17:29,652
Why is that?

361
00:17:31,531 --> 00:17:32,612
I'm now openly competing

362
00:17:32,612 --> 00:17:33,291
with Dong Yue

363
00:17:33,291 --> 00:17:34,372
and Tang Lide.

364
00:17:35,251 --> 00:17:36,652
I fear Dong Yue will trouble you.

365
00:17:38,132 --> 00:17:39,491
How can he trouble me?

366
00:17:39,771 --> 00:17:40,451
Thanks.

367
00:17:41,092 --> 00:17:42,251
By taking away my clients?

368
00:17:42,372 --> 00:17:43,092
My clients

369
00:17:43,092 --> 00:17:44,731
are kept through my own relationships.

370
00:17:46,211 --> 00:17:47,172
And I think

371
00:17:47,372 --> 00:17:48,491
Dong Yue's a good person.

372
00:17:48,572 --> 00:17:49,352
He won't do that.

373
00:17:50,731 --> 00:17:52,211
Maybe Dong Yue won't.

374
00:17:54,132 --> 00:17:55,011
What about others?

375
00:17:56,971 --> 00:17:57,652
Others?

376
00:17:59,372 --> 00:18:00,491
You mean Yu Wei'e?

377
00:18:02,211 --> 00:18:03,251
Yu Wei'e...

378
00:18:07,531 --> 00:18:08,051
Yeah.

379
00:18:08,652 --> 00:18:10,332
That scoundrel usually

380
00:18:10,332 --> 00:18:11,572
does talk big,

381
00:18:11,572 --> 00:18:13,132
but he rarely spreads rumors so openly.

382
00:18:13,491 --> 00:18:14,491
So what's his intention?

383
00:18:14,852 --> 00:18:15,572
Taking sides?

384
00:18:17,731 --> 00:18:19,572
Showing his loyalty to Dong Yue.

385
00:18:22,056 --> 00:18:23,304
My gosh.

386
00:18:24,132 --> 00:18:25,332
Am I being naive again?

387
00:18:37,051 --> 00:18:38,051
I'm leaving first.

388
00:18:38,771 --> 00:18:39,372
Bye.

389
00:18:39,412 --> 00:18:40,132
Bye.

390
00:18:46,892 --> 00:18:47,392
Boss,

391
00:18:47,731 --> 00:18:48,412
got a minute?

392
00:18:48,572 --> 00:18:49,132
Care to chat?

393
00:18:50,132 --> 00:18:51,132
Sure, have a seat.

394
00:18:58,291 --> 00:18:59,051
Boss,

395
00:19:00,332 --> 00:19:01,731
about that matter

396
00:19:02,051 --> 00:19:03,652
between me and Yu Wei'e,

397
00:19:06,572 --> 00:19:07,372
I...

398
00:19:12,812 --> 00:19:15,132
Forget it. I won't beat around the bush.

399
00:19:15,932 --> 00:19:18,092
Actually, I wanted to
talk about Zhao Mei.

400
00:19:19,771 --> 00:19:21,211
About Zhao Mei's current situation,

401
00:19:22,132 --> 00:19:23,892
I know what everyone is thinking.

402
00:19:24,531 --> 00:19:26,691
But I still have some heartfelt thoughts

403
00:19:27,172 --> 00:19:28,291
to share with you.

404
00:19:29,612 --> 00:19:30,572
Zhao Mei and I

405
00:19:31,132 --> 00:19:33,211
have been best friends
since over a decade ago.

406
00:19:33,812 --> 00:19:36,451
She worked in promotions
while I handled sales all these years.

407
00:19:36,812 --> 00:19:38,291
Work and friendship are separate.

408
00:19:38,291 --> 00:19:40,172
I always keep them that way.

409
00:19:40,612 --> 00:19:42,051
Besides, I don't want a promotion.

410
00:19:42,291 --> 00:19:44,372
I just want to maintain

411
00:19:44,372 --> 00:19:46,412
the clients I already handle well.

412
00:19:46,812 --> 00:19:49,731
So you really don't need
to worry about me on this.

413
00:19:50,612 --> 00:19:51,771
Let me put it this way.

414
00:19:53,051 --> 00:19:55,332
Zhao Mei and I are best friends,

415
00:19:56,132 --> 00:19:58,771
but you're my boss.

416
00:20:02,372 --> 00:20:03,132
You're being blunt.

417
00:20:03,132 --> 00:20:04,132
So I'll be blunt too.

418
00:20:06,051 --> 00:20:07,451
In your opinion, if Zhao Mei

419
00:20:08,731 --> 00:20:09,771
wants this position,

420
00:20:10,451 --> 00:20:11,291
what are her chances?

421
00:20:16,372 --> 00:20:18,251
How would I know?

422
00:20:19,211 --> 00:20:21,451
That depends on
what the top executives think.

423
00:20:21,852 --> 00:20:23,531
Which one is she close with?

424
00:20:28,172 --> 00:20:29,932
The executives' thoughts?

425
00:20:29,932 --> 00:20:31,652
I... I don't know.

426
00:20:32,572 --> 00:20:34,051
But during the drinks,

427
00:20:34,051 --> 00:20:35,051
she seemed pretty close

428
00:20:35,051 --> 00:20:36,051
with every executive.

429
00:20:38,211 --> 00:20:40,731
During the drinks?
Mr. Xu even promised me

430
00:20:41,332 --> 00:20:42,291
he'd always back me.

431
00:20:43,412 --> 00:20:44,251
That's true.

432
00:20:49,892 --> 00:20:50,971
Here is a task for you.

433
00:20:51,812 --> 00:20:52,652
Just name it.

434
00:20:53,412 --> 00:20:55,491
Zhao Mei was promoted
by Mr. Xu personally.

435
00:20:56,172 --> 00:20:58,332
She must've done a lot for him,

436
00:20:59,852 --> 00:21:01,172
with all the promotion funds

437
00:21:01,932 --> 00:21:02,771
passing through her.

438
00:21:04,652 --> 00:21:05,152
Right?

439
00:21:11,572 --> 00:21:12,572
I don't know.

440
00:21:13,892 --> 00:21:15,051
Besides, she wouldn't tell me

441
00:21:15,132 --> 00:21:16,691
about that kind of thing.

442
00:21:20,332 --> 00:21:22,291
Then let's go back
to the simpler question.

443
00:21:22,372 --> 00:21:23,531
Who among the executives

444
00:21:25,612 --> 00:21:26,731
do you think Zhao Mei

445
00:21:27,691 --> 00:21:29,691
is closest with privately?

446
00:21:29,691 --> 00:21:30,652
Outside of the drinks.

447
00:21:33,412 --> 00:21:34,771
I honestly haven't paid attention.

448
00:21:35,691 --> 00:21:36,372
Because when

449
00:21:36,372 --> 00:21:37,892
Zhao Mei and I meet privately,

450
00:21:37,892 --> 00:21:38,691
it's just us.

451
00:21:38,691 --> 00:21:39,971
And with Ms. Qi?

452
00:21:42,372 --> 00:21:42,892
Ms. Qi?

453
00:21:43,211 --> 00:21:44,332
And the Asia-Pacific region?

454
00:21:45,812 --> 00:21:47,412
She had a history
with Gao Jiawei, right?

455
00:21:56,451 --> 00:21:56,951
Well,

456
00:21:57,892 --> 00:21:58,451
boss,

457
00:21:58,852 --> 00:22:00,572
I've noted your questions.

458
00:22:01,332 --> 00:22:02,491
I'll pay attention next time.

459
00:22:07,771 --> 00:22:08,691
I'll head out now.

460
00:22:09,852 --> 00:22:10,812
See you.

461
00:22:13,132 --> 00:22:13,632
Danning.

462
00:22:17,051 --> 00:22:18,372
Do you really think Zhao Mei

463
00:22:19,332 --> 00:22:19,852
is up to it?

464
00:22:25,372 --> 00:22:26,372
I believe

465
00:22:30,771 --> 00:22:33,652
you're still better in sales operations.

466
00:22:44,491 --> 00:22:46,092
(She clearly doesn't want to help you.)

467
00:22:46,172 --> 00:22:47,011
Yeah.

468
00:22:48,812 --> 00:22:49,771
She's quite loyal.

469
00:22:51,112 --> 00:22:53,132
She and Zhao Mei
started together as promoters.

470
00:22:53,372 --> 00:22:54,812
Friends from humble beginnings.

471
00:22:55,451 --> 00:22:57,291
It's fine. She's not a key player.

472
00:22:58,372 --> 00:22:59,172
Interesting.

473
00:23:00,451 --> 00:23:01,612
Shen Xing's mother

474
00:23:02,412 --> 00:23:03,812
was also a sales lay back then.

475
00:23:04,691 --> 00:23:05,191
Really?

476
00:23:06,812 --> 00:23:08,531
Many in our generation in this business

477
00:23:09,291 --> 00:23:11,652
ended up marrying sales ladies.

478
00:23:13,211 --> 00:23:16,332
Our work often went past midnight.

479
00:23:17,372 --> 00:23:20,652
Dating people with other jobs
was impossible.

480
00:23:21,132 --> 00:23:22,291
And we couldn't exactly

481
00:23:22,291 --> 00:23:24,412
find a girlfriend in bars or clubs.

482
00:23:25,172 --> 00:23:27,491
In the end, we'd be only surrounded
by colleagues:

483
00:23:28,051 --> 00:23:31,092
stock clerks, sales ladies,
and female coworkers.

484
00:23:31,852 --> 00:23:34,251
The sales ladies
were the prettiest among them.

485
00:23:34,932 --> 00:23:37,852
Back then, sales ladies
had excellent qualities.

486
00:23:37,892 --> 00:23:40,691
Each one was handpicked.

487
00:23:41,011 --> 00:23:43,691
Tall at 1.7 meters, with curves.

488
00:23:44,812 --> 00:23:46,852
Beautiful college graduates.

489
00:23:52,291 --> 00:23:53,332
Liang Danning.

490
00:23:54,412 --> 00:23:55,612
She's genuinely impressive.

491
00:24:08,572 --> 00:24:09,092
Jin,

492
00:24:09,932 --> 00:24:13,011
last time your wife set the dog
on that girl and injured her.

493
00:24:13,332 --> 00:24:15,332
You need to resolve this quickly.

494
00:24:17,771 --> 00:24:18,652
Such dawdling.

495
00:24:20,332 --> 00:24:20,832
Come on.

496
00:24:33,723 --> 00:24:35,176
(Shanshui Hall)

497
00:24:35,531 --> 00:24:36,132
Miss,

498
00:24:36,491 --> 00:24:37,691
who are you looking for?

499
00:24:42,491 --> 00:24:43,372
Hello.

500
00:24:44,051 --> 00:24:45,572
I'm here to see Mr. Shen.

501
00:24:46,491 --> 00:24:47,372
Please come in.

502
00:24:51,812 --> 00:24:54,812
What a fully high-tech smart home.

503
00:24:55,051 --> 00:24:56,132
Go straight downhill.

504
00:24:57,412 --> 00:24:58,291
Thank you.

505
00:25:17,812 --> 00:25:19,291
Is this the right way?

506
00:25:33,332 --> 00:25:36,691
(Prefers getting straight
to the point. Got it.)

507
00:25:37,771 --> 00:25:39,731
Good evening, Ms. Liang.

508
00:25:40,051 --> 00:25:41,572
Mr. Shen is waiting for you.

509
00:25:42,612 --> 00:25:44,731
Mr. Shen, sorry I'm late.

510
00:25:45,412 --> 00:25:46,332
This way, please.

511
00:25:50,612 --> 00:25:52,011
Go straight and then turn left.

512
00:25:52,291 --> 00:25:53,211
Through the lounge.

513
00:26:05,691 --> 00:26:06,251
Mr. Shen.

514
00:26:07,932 --> 00:26:09,491
So sorry I'm late.

515
00:26:09,491 --> 00:26:10,372
Traffic was heavy.

516
00:26:10,932 --> 00:26:11,731
It's fine.

517
00:26:12,612 --> 00:26:13,652
A few minutes late

518
00:26:13,932 --> 00:26:15,731
is nothing for a lady.

519
00:26:16,572 --> 00:26:18,132
This is for you.

520
00:26:18,691 --> 00:26:20,011
How thoughtful. Thank you.

521
00:26:20,531 --> 00:26:21,572
I'd like a cup of tea.

522
00:26:22,372 --> 00:26:23,132
Just a moment.

523
00:26:25,531 --> 00:26:27,451
You can tell it what you want to drink.

524
00:26:28,011 --> 00:26:29,211
But you have to speak

525
00:26:29,572 --> 00:26:31,491
Mandarin or standard English.

526
00:26:32,251 --> 00:26:33,932
Dialects won't work.

527
00:26:34,172 --> 00:26:34,932
Really?

528
00:26:35,051 --> 00:26:35,812
Try it.

529
00:26:38,051 --> 00:26:40,491
Hello, give me a cup of tea.

530
00:26:40,612 --> 00:26:41,172
I'm sorry.

531
00:26:41,612 --> 00:26:43,172
I didn't understand your question.

532
00:26:45,051 --> 00:26:45,572
Hello.

533
00:26:45,572 --> 00:26:47,251
Please give me a cup of tea. Thank you.

534
00:26:47,372 --> 00:26:48,211
Just a moment.

535
00:26:49,251 --> 00:26:50,291
Are you Shanghainese?

536
00:26:50,932 --> 00:26:53,011
No, I just know a little Shanghainese.

537
00:26:53,652 --> 00:26:54,920
You're gifted with languages.

538
00:26:55,172 --> 00:26:56,291
Not really.

539
00:26:56,932 --> 00:26:57,971
Just with dialects.

540
00:26:57,971 --> 00:26:59,172
No matter where I go,

541
00:26:59,172 --> 00:27:00,172
within three months,

542
00:27:00,172 --> 00:27:01,640
I can argue in the local dialect.

543
00:27:02,211 --> 00:27:03,172
That's impressive.

544
00:27:03,172 --> 00:27:04,092
Just so-so.

545
00:27:08,691 --> 00:27:09,771
Surprised?

546
00:27:10,172 --> 00:27:11,011
I've only seen

547
00:27:11,011 --> 00:27:12,531
this kind of robot in hotels.

548
00:27:13,191 --> 00:27:13,691
No.

549
00:27:13,691 --> 00:27:15,944
It's the first time I've seen one
with a defined waist.

550
00:27:16,451 --> 00:27:18,132
You prefer robots to people
at your place?

551
00:27:18,132 --> 00:27:19,172
Why would you say that?

552
00:27:19,812 --> 00:27:20,572
Come sit over here.

553
00:27:26,291 --> 00:27:26,971
Please sit.

554
00:27:27,211 --> 00:27:27,971
Thank you.

555
00:27:28,612 --> 00:27:30,211
Of course there are real people here.

556
00:27:30,771 --> 00:27:32,011
Like nanny and driver.

557
00:27:33,412 --> 00:27:36,011
I invested in a smart home company.

558
00:27:36,172 --> 00:27:38,251
I asked them to retrofit my place first.

559
00:27:39,612 --> 00:27:40,852
It started as a fun thing.

560
00:27:41,332 --> 00:27:43,172
But they didn't make any money
for years.

561
00:27:43,731 --> 00:27:45,731
So I supported them
with liquor sales profits.

562
00:27:46,731 --> 00:27:48,572
Unexpectedly, these past few years,

563
00:27:49,451 --> 00:27:50,491
the tides turned.

564
00:27:51,372 --> 00:27:52,932
Liquor sales slumped.

565
00:27:53,771 --> 00:27:55,731
But that company took off instead.

566
00:27:56,372 --> 00:27:57,812
People are chasing to invest now.

567
00:27:58,572 --> 00:27:59,531
They're planning an IPO.

568
00:28:00,451 --> 00:28:02,291
That proves you're the God of Wealth.

569
00:28:02,531 --> 00:28:03,771
No matter how the winds shift,

570
00:28:03,971 --> 00:28:05,372
the opportunity is always with you.

571
00:28:07,251 --> 00:28:08,332
Would you like dinner?

572
00:28:09,211 --> 00:28:11,852
Great. I've never eaten food
made by a robot.

573
00:28:12,092 --> 00:28:13,251
Not here.

574
00:28:13,852 --> 00:28:14,888
However good robots are,

575
00:28:15,211 --> 00:28:16,852
food should still be made
by real people.

576
00:28:17,971 --> 00:28:20,172
There are a few nice restaurants nearby.

577
00:28:20,491 --> 00:28:21,372
What would you like?

578
00:28:23,491 --> 00:28:24,211
Mr. Shen,

579
00:28:24,531 --> 00:28:27,491
you saved me last time.
Let me treat you to this meal, okay?

580
00:28:29,491 --> 00:28:29,991
Okay.

581
00:28:31,900 --> 00:28:37,288
(Xing's Hot Pot)

582
00:28:38,852 --> 00:28:39,491
Here.

583
00:28:40,291 --> 00:28:41,771
Try their soup.

584
00:28:41,892 --> 00:28:43,932
Secret recipe. Very tasty.

585
00:28:48,011 --> 00:28:48,731
How is it?

586
00:28:50,011 --> 00:28:50,572
Very fresh.

587
00:28:51,132 --> 00:28:51,731
Refreshing.

588
00:28:52,051 --> 00:28:52,892
Thank you.

589
00:28:54,652 --> 00:28:57,612
And a sweet aftertaste.
Did they add sugarcane?

590
00:28:58,372 --> 00:29:01,011
Yes. Clever. They did add sugarcane.

591
00:29:01,531 --> 00:29:03,812
Impressive. We did put sugarcane in it.

592
00:29:03,932 --> 00:29:04,432
Right?

593
00:29:05,051 --> 00:29:06,892
These clams just arrived this afternoon.

594
00:29:07,612 --> 00:29:08,572
The meat is very sweet.

595
00:29:09,332 --> 00:29:10,771
Please try them.

596
00:29:10,892 --> 00:29:11,572
Thank you.

597
00:29:11,691 --> 00:29:13,211
Ma'am, you're too kind.

598
00:29:13,731 --> 00:29:14,731
Please eat.

599
00:29:14,731 --> 00:29:16,332
- You're too kind.
- Thank you, ma'am.

600
00:29:16,572 --> 00:29:17,731
Just eat.

601
00:29:21,771 --> 00:29:22,731
Want a bottle of liquor?

602
00:29:24,531 --> 00:29:26,731
Your wound hasn't healed yet.
You can't drink.

603
00:29:27,291 --> 00:29:30,451
It's been seven days.
And I started drinking yesterday.

604
00:29:30,691 --> 00:29:32,172
Well? How about a bottle?

605
00:29:33,011 --> 00:29:34,211
Better not order it.

606
00:29:35,291 --> 00:29:36,812
I've been taking meds these days.

607
00:29:37,652 --> 00:29:38,612
I can't drink alcohol.

608
00:29:39,251 --> 00:29:40,892
But when you texted me yesterday,

609
00:29:40,892 --> 00:29:42,491
you said you were drinking at Cocoon.

610
00:29:47,652 --> 00:29:48,971
Don't say it out loud.

611
00:29:51,572 --> 00:29:54,092
Sorry. Pretend I didn't say that.

612
00:29:55,612 --> 00:29:57,251
How can you be so adorable?

613
00:29:58,092 --> 00:29:59,451
Just that adorable.

614
00:30:01,491 --> 00:30:03,372
Try this. Be careful, it's hot.

615
00:30:06,011 --> 00:30:06,511
Look.

616
00:30:07,691 --> 00:30:09,172
The cross-section of this char siu

617
00:30:09,531 --> 00:30:11,251
has over five layers. That's rare.

618
00:30:12,011 --> 00:30:13,332
Glad you like it.

619
00:30:14,451 --> 00:30:16,011
I'll take you somewhere else next time.

620
00:30:16,372 --> 00:30:17,691
Their flower crabs...

621
00:30:19,291 --> 00:30:20,092
Flower crabs?

622
00:30:20,372 --> 00:30:21,531
They're my favorite.

623
00:30:22,051 --> 00:30:23,011
Then it's a deal.

624
00:30:29,092 --> 00:30:31,132
Your necklace is quite unique.

625
00:30:32,531 --> 00:30:34,011
I had it blessed at the temple.

626
00:30:34,691 --> 00:30:35,771
It's a bronze mirror.

627
00:30:36,291 --> 00:30:37,572
Does it have special meaning?

628
00:30:39,092 --> 00:30:40,612
Absolutely.

629
00:30:41,251 --> 00:30:43,852
Mrs. Jin wanted to strike me
with that peachwood sword, right?

630
00:30:44,051 --> 00:30:44,771
So I thought,

631
00:30:45,172 --> 00:30:47,251
next time she attacks,
I'll wear this mirror

632
00:30:47,251 --> 00:30:49,172
and reflect her energy right back.

633
00:30:50,451 --> 00:30:51,251
I mean it.

634
00:30:52,011 --> 00:30:53,572
Knowing I was visiting you,

635
00:30:53,771 --> 00:30:55,731
I even brought

636
00:30:56,771 --> 00:30:57,612
a dog-beating staff.

637
00:31:07,976 --> 00:31:08,712
Hello?

638
00:31:09,011 --> 00:31:10,291
Pay your husband's debt.

639
00:31:10,812 --> 00:31:11,771
Or I'll come for it.

640
00:31:12,092 --> 00:31:12,652
Wrong number.

641
00:31:15,132 --> 00:31:15,652
What's wrong?

642
00:31:16,652 --> 00:31:17,491
Robocall.

643
00:31:22,211 --> 00:31:22,932
Mom.

644
00:31:24,812 --> 00:31:25,771
Good girl.

645
00:31:26,011 --> 00:31:26,932
Have you eaten?

646
00:31:26,932 --> 00:31:27,572
Yes, I have.

647
00:31:27,572 --> 00:31:28,771
Yes? How about Grandma?

648
00:31:31,771 --> 00:31:32,531
Mom.

649
00:31:34,291 --> 00:31:35,852
How'd it go? Client satisfied?

650
00:31:36,451 --> 00:31:37,812
Beyond satisfied.

651
00:31:38,572 --> 00:31:41,572
Big shots like them
have tried every delicacy.

652
00:31:41,572 --> 00:31:43,612
They've seen all the fancy venues.

653
00:31:44,011 --> 00:31:46,172
They don't care about food anymore.

654
00:31:46,172 --> 00:31:48,572
It's our restaurant's down-to-earth vibe

655
00:31:48,572 --> 00:31:50,332
that's missing from their lives.

656
00:31:52,011 --> 00:31:52,812
Look at you.

657
00:31:53,251 --> 00:31:56,211
If you studied as hard
as you analyze clients,

658
00:31:56,372 --> 00:31:58,051
you'd have gone to college.

659
00:31:58,251 --> 00:32:00,612
You always turn everything
into a lecture.

660
00:32:01,092 --> 00:32:02,771
Ma'am, can I get a receipt?

661
00:32:02,771 --> 00:32:04,612
Sure, coming right up.

662
00:32:04,932 --> 00:32:06,251
I'll see off the client first.

663
00:32:15,791 --> 00:32:16,291
All paid.

664
00:32:16,291 --> 00:32:17,491
Here's what you requested.

665
00:32:18,011 --> 00:32:18,812
Wait in the car.

666
00:32:18,812 --> 00:32:19,312
Okay.

667
00:32:19,812 --> 00:32:21,451
Jin asked me to give you this gift

668
00:32:21,531 --> 00:32:23,172
to make amends and apologize.

669
00:32:23,211 --> 00:32:25,771
No need.
Mr. Jin already ordered liquor from me.

670
00:32:25,932 --> 00:32:27,572
The liquor order benefited your company.

671
00:32:28,491 --> 00:32:30,572
This gift is his personal apology.

672
00:32:32,291 --> 00:32:34,011
Jin's been my friend for over a decade.

673
00:32:34,491 --> 00:32:36,332
He's decent and low-key.

674
00:32:36,771 --> 00:32:37,771
But his wife

675
00:32:39,092 --> 00:32:39,880
is very sensitive.

676
00:32:41,412 --> 00:32:44,211
He wanted to deliver it personally
but worried it'd be awkward.

677
00:32:44,971 --> 00:32:46,092
So he sent it to my place.

678
00:32:47,251 --> 00:32:49,412
Just take it. No need to feel awkward.

679
00:32:50,812 --> 00:32:52,132
Alright then. Thanks.

680
00:32:52,892 --> 00:32:53,652
I need to go.

681
00:32:54,251 --> 00:32:55,011
I'll walk you out.

682
00:32:55,172 --> 00:32:55,672
Okay.

683
00:32:59,011 --> 00:32:59,812
(Xing's Hot Pot)
I had a great time.

684
00:33:00,771 --> 00:33:02,771
Thanks for treating me
to such delicious food.

685
00:33:04,491 --> 00:33:06,172
It was so affordable. I feel bad.

686
00:33:06,412 --> 00:33:07,172
Don't mention it.

687
00:33:07,531 --> 00:33:09,491
I've got something else
and can't drive you home.

688
00:33:09,892 --> 00:33:10,812
Can you return alone?

689
00:33:11,731 --> 00:33:12,332
Of course.

690
00:33:12,691 --> 00:33:14,051
I'll wait with you for your ride.

691
00:33:16,251 --> 00:33:17,251
Alright, I'll call a car.

692
00:33:19,372 --> 00:33:20,491
Are you and Zhao Mei

693
00:33:21,612 --> 00:33:22,291
friends?

694
00:33:22,812 --> 00:33:23,612
Yeah.

695
00:33:23,771 --> 00:33:25,132
Best friends for over a decade.

696
00:33:25,971 --> 00:33:27,011
Do you know

697
00:33:27,771 --> 00:33:29,812
Barry was going to sue her?

698
00:33:30,731 --> 00:33:31,812
I know about that.

699
00:33:32,531 --> 00:33:34,211
But thankfully they settled.

700
00:33:34,291 --> 00:33:35,332
Probably the top brass

701
00:33:35,332 --> 00:33:37,132
eventually approved her approach.

702
00:33:37,132 --> 00:33:38,092
Approved? No.

703
00:33:39,211 --> 00:33:40,971
How could Barry possibly approve of her?

704
00:33:42,251 --> 00:33:43,451
It's all just for show.

705
00:33:44,412 --> 00:33:45,491
Fear for public opinion.

706
00:33:47,172 --> 00:33:48,291
She'll face tough times.

707
00:33:49,531 --> 00:33:50,172
Really?

708
00:33:51,011 --> 00:33:51,812
Definitely.

709
00:33:54,011 --> 00:33:56,771
Business thrives on harmony.

710
00:33:57,092 --> 00:33:59,572
All that online support and cheering

711
00:33:59,971 --> 00:34:01,572
are all fake, just loud shouting.

712
00:34:03,771 --> 00:34:04,892
In normal life,

713
00:34:05,731 --> 00:34:07,172
will you work with someone

714
00:34:08,011 --> 00:34:10,011
who flips tables at the drop of a hat?

715
00:34:11,852 --> 00:34:12,932
If you were the boss,

716
00:34:13,531 --> 00:34:14,892
would you dare use a subordinate

717
00:34:15,252 --> 00:34:16,892
who goes to extremes when unhappy

718
00:34:17,252 --> 00:34:18,531
and publicly insults you?

719
00:34:20,212 --> 00:34:20,971
Impossible.

720
00:34:23,252 --> 00:34:24,051
Unlike you.

721
00:34:25,412 --> 00:34:26,292
You handle problems

722
00:34:27,212 --> 00:34:27,852
with great tact.

723
00:34:28,571 --> 00:34:29,372
Me?

724
00:34:30,372 --> 00:34:31,812
My situation is different from hers.

725
00:34:32,531 --> 00:34:33,611
Why is it different?

726
00:34:34,292 --> 00:34:35,252
Women shouldn't

727
00:34:36,571 --> 00:34:37,692
push themselves too hard.

728
00:34:38,692 --> 00:34:40,772
The return on pushing too hard
is very low.

729
00:34:46,772 --> 00:34:47,692
Buzz off.

730
00:34:49,252 --> 00:34:50,091
Who's an eyesore?

731
00:34:50,531 --> 00:34:51,571
Who's an eyesore?

732
00:34:53,932 --> 00:34:54,611
(Nine years ago)
Slow down.

733
00:34:55,332 --> 00:34:56,131
Who started it?

734
00:34:56,571 --> 00:34:57,372
Liang Danning?

735
00:34:58,091 --> 00:35:00,531
Not her. I started it.

736
00:35:01,491 --> 00:35:02,292
I started it.

737
00:35:03,212 --> 00:35:04,812
Their insults were too vicious.

738
00:35:04,812 --> 00:35:06,451
They tried to extort 500 yuan from us.

739
00:35:06,892 --> 00:35:08,971
I got so mad I threw beer on them.

740
00:35:09,732 --> 00:35:11,451
How many times have I stressed this?

741
00:35:12,252 --> 00:35:13,531
The stores strictly prohibit

742
00:35:13,932 --> 00:35:15,491
promoters from using aggressive tactics

743
00:35:15,651 --> 00:35:16,531
for sales.

744
00:35:17,571 --> 00:35:20,171
It was just 500 yuan.
You could've given it to them first

745
00:35:20,692 --> 00:35:22,812
and then called your supervisor
or even me later on

746
00:35:23,292 --> 00:35:24,332
to get the money back.

747
00:35:25,292 --> 00:35:27,091
Instead, you fought, and you started it.

748
00:35:29,051 --> 00:35:30,372
Aren't you usually smart?

749
00:35:30,772 --> 00:35:31,732
Why act so foolish now?

750
00:35:33,292 --> 00:35:34,292
It's all my fault.

751
00:35:35,011 --> 00:35:36,131
Boss, punish me.

752
00:35:38,852 --> 00:35:40,571
Ask your supervisor to transfer you.

753
00:35:41,171 --> 00:35:42,692
Listen, don't let it happen again.

754
00:35:43,692 --> 00:35:44,611
Thank you, boss.

755
00:35:44,692 --> 00:35:46,131
Thank you, boss.

756
00:35:49,292 --> 00:35:50,971
Why did you say you started it?

757
00:35:51,332 --> 00:35:52,651
The boss likes me.

758
00:35:52,732 --> 00:35:54,772
If I say I started it,
he won't do anything to me.

759
00:35:54,772 --> 00:35:56,212
But if he knew you started it,

760
00:35:56,212 --> 00:35:57,611
he might have fired you.

761
00:35:58,531 --> 00:35:59,651
You're so smart.

762
00:36:00,212 --> 00:36:00,971
Don't touch me.

763
00:36:01,892 --> 00:36:02,812
I'm so sorry.

764
00:36:03,051 --> 00:36:04,332
I'll give you a massage later.

765
00:36:57,292 --> 00:36:57,812
Mom.

766
00:36:58,412 --> 00:36:59,491
Why aren't you asleep yet?

767
00:37:00,292 --> 00:37:01,212
I'm not sleepy.

768
00:37:02,171 --> 00:37:02,932
What's wrong?

769
00:37:06,252 --> 00:37:08,611
Mom, is this a new purse you bought?

770
00:37:08,971 --> 00:37:10,732
No, someone gave it to me.

771
00:37:11,252 --> 00:37:11,932
It's not pretty.

772
00:37:12,332 --> 00:37:13,332
Not pretty?

773
00:37:13,971 --> 00:37:16,531
How about I sell it online?

774
00:37:16,732 --> 00:37:19,491
Don't sell it. If you like it, keep it.

775
00:37:19,571 --> 00:37:21,772
Keep it? But I have no occasion for it.

776
00:37:22,091 --> 00:37:23,932
And carrying it
might make people jealous.

777
00:37:27,451 --> 00:37:29,971
You could carry it
to my parent-teacher conference.

778
00:37:32,051 --> 00:37:33,651
Good idea.

779
00:37:34,531 --> 00:37:35,971
I can carry this

780
00:37:35,971 --> 00:37:39,011
to your parent-teacher conference.

781
00:37:40,131 --> 00:37:40,971
I got that.

782
00:37:40,971 --> 00:37:43,491
Are you blaming me for missing
the parent-teacher conference?

783
00:37:43,692 --> 00:37:44,892
No, I'm not.

784
00:37:45,171 --> 00:37:46,812
Yes, you are.

785
00:37:47,971 --> 00:37:49,091
It's my fault.

786
00:37:49,571 --> 00:37:52,531
I promise
I will definitely attend the next one.

787
00:37:53,252 --> 00:37:55,491
Mom, can I sleep with you tonight?

788
00:37:56,131 --> 00:37:58,852
What a coincidence,
I wanted to sleep with you too.

789
00:37:59,412 --> 00:38:00,531
Little monkey, time for bed.

790
00:38:06,292 --> 00:38:06,971
Time to sleep.

791
00:38:06,971 --> 00:38:07,692
Lie down properly.

792
00:38:08,531 --> 00:38:09,571
Tuck yourself in.

793
00:38:09,571 --> 00:38:10,091
Okay.

794
00:38:16,932 --> 00:38:19,571
Weiwei, even though
I didn't go to the conference,

795
00:38:20,171 --> 00:38:21,611
the teacher called and said

796
00:38:21,611 --> 00:38:23,212
your grades have improved a lot.

797
00:38:23,732 --> 00:38:26,292
I'll improve even more.
I want to be first in class.

798
00:38:27,292 --> 00:38:29,131
You're working so hard? Why?

799
00:38:30,131 --> 00:38:31,412
I want to earn money.

800
00:38:33,131 --> 00:38:37,212
Lots and lots of money
to help you pay off debts.

801
00:39:37,203 --> 00:39:41,943
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

802
00:39:46,393 --> 00:39:48,313
♪Too much of shame♪

803
00:39:48,659 --> 00:39:51,455
♪To waste it crying♪

804
00:39:53,913 --> 00:39:55,833
♪Leave all behind you♪

805
00:39:55,833 --> 00:39:58,113
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

806
00:39:58,233 --> 00:40:00,462
♪You know how far you've gone♪

807
00:40:00,597 --> 00:40:02,873
♪In the fire you rise again♪

808
00:40:03,059 --> 00:40:05,419
♪You made it through the worst♪

809
00:40:05,557 --> 00:40:07,761
♪The best is yet to come♪

810
00:40:08,004 --> 00:40:10,144
♪The best is yet to come♪

811
00:40:12,846 --> 00:40:14,169
♪Isn't it magical♪

812
00:40:14,169 --> 00:40:15,801
♪Listen, look,
how beautiful the night is♪

813
00:40:15,833 --> 00:40:18,300
♪With countless lights on,
is someone heartbroken again♪

814
00:40:18,300 --> 00:40:20,753
♪The sound of a heart
shattering on the ground is so crisp♪

815
00:40:20,834 --> 00:40:23,482
♪Turn on a light.
A lonely heart needs comfort♪

816
00:40:23,571 --> 00:40:26,102
♪Sweat, toil, dawn, dusk♪

817
00:40:26,182 --> 00:40:28,404
♪Devaluing self-respect
just for some hot food♪

818
00:40:28,546 --> 00:40:29,627
♪But I don't want to♪

819
00:40:29,736 --> 00:40:32,002
♪Sell dignity at a price,
trampling on past vows♪

820
00:40:32,118 --> 00:40:33,183
♪Until 3 AM♪

821
00:40:33,354 --> 00:40:34,559
♪Locking dreams away in a drawer♪

822
00:40:34,713 --> 00:40:35,946
♪Just to earn some meager profit♪

823
00:40:36,037 --> 00:40:38,401
♪No matter how hard I try,
it only brings sobs♪

824
00:40:38,548 --> 00:40:42,958
♪Renewing yearly, gone with no return,
teetering, utterly bland♪

825
00:40:57,683 --> 00:40:59,119
♪Leave all behind you♪

826
00:40:59,223 --> 00:41:01,710
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

827
00:41:01,893 --> 00:41:04,022
♪You know how far you've gone♪

828
00:41:04,209 --> 00:41:06,549
♪In the fire you rise again♪

829
00:41:06,617 --> 00:41:08,883
♪You made it through the worst♪

830
00:41:09,243 --> 00:41:11,321
♪The best is yet to come♪

831
00:41:11,570 --> 00:41:13,740
♪The best is yet to come♪

832
00:41:16,441 --> 00:41:17,593
♪Isn't it magical♪

833
00:41:17,593 --> 00:41:21,239
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

834
00:41:21,273 --> 00:41:23,129
♪And I see them sparkling♪

835
00:41:23,353 --> 00:41:25,484
♪Nobody knows♪

836
00:41:26,105 --> 00:41:28,015
♪What tomorrow brings♪

837
00:41:28,281 --> 00:41:30,604
♪You made it through the worst♪

838
00:41:30,791 --> 00:41:32,999
♪The best is yet to come♪

839
00:41:33,286 --> 00:41:35,435
♪The best is yet to come♪

840
00:41:35,731 --> 00:41:37,145
♪Isn't it magical♪

841
00:41:37,145 --> 00:41:39,357
♪Feeling uneasy,
yet no one's chasing me♪

842
00:41:39,431 --> 00:41:41,785
♪Retreating step by step,
everything turning to ash♪

843
00:41:41,785 --> 00:41:42,873
♪I'm silent, I'm roaring♪

844
